WEBVTT

00:00.245 --> 00:01.812
<i>Previously on "Heartland:"</i>

00:02.130 --> 00:03.697
- Hey!
- Hey, how's it goin'?

00:03.765 --> 00:05.299
I could use, uh,
15 more minutes.

00:05.366 --> 00:06.467
<i>You don't got it.</i>

00:06.568 --> 00:07.535
So, who's next?

00:08.737 --> 00:09.770
Oh!

00:09.838 --> 00:10.871
He still hasn't called.

00:10.939 --> 00:11.738
Who?

00:11.806 --> 00:13.673
Who do you think?
Peter!

00:13.741 --> 00:15.241
Have you tried
calling him?

00:15.309 --> 00:16.341
No!

00:16.410 --> 00:18.478
I don't wanna
seem desperate!

00:18.546 --> 00:19.879
<i>You lied to her!
You took her mom's money,</i>

00:19.947 --> 00:21.714
and now you won't even
fix her hot water heater.

00:21.782 --> 00:22.982
Just keep it up, man.

00:23.050 --> 00:24.484
You're never gonna get
your trailer back.

00:24.552 --> 00:26.085
We were married
a lot of years,

00:26.153 --> 00:28.487
we spent our honeymoon
right here.

00:28.555 --> 00:29.588
And then uh,

00:29.656 --> 00:31.356
then after her funeral, I,

00:31.424 --> 00:32.925
I spread her ashes
in the river.

00:32.992 --> 00:34.560
That sounds like
quite a love affair.

00:35.627 --> 00:37.496
I love this song.

00:37.564 --> 00:39.297
<i>Your gramma could sing,
that's for sure.</i>

00:45.537 --> 00:46.571
<i>It's fine, Lou.</i>

00:46.638 --> 00:47.939
<i>I don't have to be perfect.</i>

00:48.039 --> 00:50.207
Just hold still.

00:50.275 --> 00:53.043
I'll be sittin' still
on a hard bench

00:53.111 --> 00:55.947
for the next two
or more hours.

00:56.014 --> 00:57.247
I barely know
these people,

00:57.315 --> 00:59.649
why don't they just elope
or something?

00:59.717 --> 01:00.450
<i>Hello!</i>

01:02.353 --> 01:03.887
Ohhh... whoa!

01:03.955 --> 01:06.222
Don't you look nice!

01:06.290 --> 01:07.657
And don't you
look handsome!

01:07.725 --> 01:08.992
I love your outfit, Lisa.

01:09.059 --> 01:10.159
It's gorgeous.

01:10.227 --> 01:11.561
Paris sales.

01:11.629 --> 01:13.697
Nothing like it.

01:13.764 --> 01:14.865
You ready?

01:14.932 --> 01:16.331
Got the car all washed,
warmed up.

01:20.370 --> 01:21.971
No, I just mean...

01:22.038 --> 01:23.506
Going to a wedding,

01:23.573 --> 01:25.107
take my car?

01:25.174 --> 01:27.409
<i>What? My truck can't go
to a wedding?</i>

01:27.477 --> 01:29.678
For your information,

01:29.746 --> 01:32.446
I just washed
and polished it.

01:32.515 --> 01:35.550
I also vacuumed it,
specially,

01:35.618 --> 01:36.751
so you wouldn't get
any dirt

01:36.819 --> 01:38.820
on that beautiful
new suit of yours.

01:38.888 --> 01:41.355
Okay, then.
Your truck it is.

01:44.693 --> 01:46.561
<i>- See ya'!
- Bye!</i>

01:46.629 --> 01:48.395
Amy!

01:48.462 --> 01:50.531
Amy, have you seen
Kramer?

01:50.598 --> 01:51.632
Kramer...?

01:51.699 --> 01:53.433
Jake's new cow pony.
He escaped.

01:53.501 --> 01:54.668
<i>For like the 15th time!</i>

01:54.736 --> 01:56.369
He jumped over the paddock
fence and took off.

01:56.437 --> 01:57.638
You need to help us
find him!

01:57.705 --> 01:59.072
Well, I'm kinda busy
with Duke right now!

01:59.140 --> 02:00.507
Amy! This is important!

02:00.575 --> 02:02.910
Well, so is this!
This poor horse is grieving.

02:03.011 --> 02:04.544
Grieving?

02:04.578 --> 02:06.245
Yes! His stable-mate
died a month or so ago,

02:06.312 --> 02:08.014
and he hasn't gotten
over it.

02:08.080 --> 02:09.481
<i>So I'm tryin' to set him
up with Pegasus,</i>

02:09.550 --> 02:11.851
see if he'll be friends.

02:11.919 --> 02:13.052
<i>There's Caleb.
He'll help us.</i>

02:13.119 --> 02:14.153
C'mon!

02:14.220 --> 02:16.889
- Caleb! Hey! Caleb, wait up!
- Good. I know.

02:16.957 --> 02:18.190
I got a treat for 'ya.

02:18.258 --> 02:19.058
You want this?

02:20.492 --> 02:22.193
<i>So, you get in Friday.</i>

02:22.261 --> 02:23.127
<i>You sure?</i>

02:24.530 --> 02:25.964
You too.

02:26.032 --> 02:26.965
Okay. Bye.

02:28.467 --> 02:30.101
Oh! Wow.

02:30.169 --> 02:32.370
Paying bills, and carrying on
a romantic phone call,

02:32.438 --> 02:33.538
all at the same time?

02:33.606 --> 02:35.306
That's multi-tasking
at its finest!

02:35.407 --> 02:36.807
I'm so excited,

02:36.875 --> 02:38.075
<i>Peter's coming in
this weekend,</i>

02:38.142 --> 02:41.011
and we have the whole
dude ranch to ourselves,

02:41.079 --> 02:43.113
<i>so I figured
we'd go for a trail ride,</i>

02:43.181 --> 02:44.481
grill up some barbeque,
um...

02:44.549 --> 02:46.516
You really have to watch
this whole social director

02:46.585 --> 02:48.518
control freak thing.
Okay?

02:48.587 --> 02:51.055
Just have dinner
and let it go from there!

02:51.122 --> 02:53.489
Yeah, and since when
are you the romance guru?

02:53.557 --> 02:55.491
Oh, since I learned
from your mistakes.

02:55.559 --> 02:56.626
Ha ha.

02:56.694 --> 02:57.794
<i>I'm serious, though.</i>

02:57.861 --> 02:58.628
You don't have to plan
every minute.

02:58.696 --> 02:59.796
<i>Okay.</i>

02:59.863 --> 03:01.965
I'm excited to see him,
obviously, but...

03:02.032 --> 03:03.232
It's been like,
a month.

03:03.300 --> 03:04.767
And I don't know...

03:04.835 --> 03:06.069
What if it's awkward?

03:06.136 --> 03:07.169
It won't be.

03:07.237 --> 03:08.804
It'll be great!

03:08.871 --> 03:09.537
Yeah.

